<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-01T04:13:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-01T04:13:00-05:00" n="572" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6852: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-01T18:00:00+08:47"><hi rend="italic">May 1, 1920—6
                                    p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 2—11:57
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>141. Agreement referred to in my telegram 137, April 30, 5 p.m., has
                                been signed. Terms practically as summarized in my telegram 119,
                                April 21, 3 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Large labor day parade this morning but no disorder.</p>
                            <pb facs="0613" n="513" xml:id="pg_513"/>
                            <p>Russian press reports that Japanese Diplomatic Agent Matsudaira
                                stated that Japanese Siberian policy is not independent but is fully
                                in accord with other Allies. Denial of accuracy of this statement by
                                Matsudaira or representatives Allies has been expected by Russians
                                but has not so far appeared, which causes considerable comment.
                                Repeated to Peking and Tokyo.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>